During a press briefing aboard Air Force One, Press Secretary Sarah Sanders provided an update on President Trump's visit to Pittsburgh following the synagogue shooting. Sanders mentioned that at the synagogue, the President met with Rabbi Myers and lit Yahrzeit candles for each of the eleven victims. The President was moved by the visit and called it "very humbling and very sad." He also visited the hospital, where he met with law enforcement members and medical staff who treated the victims. The President spent time with a first responder who had been shot seven times and also met with the widow of Dr. Richard Gottfried. Sanders mentioned that the President wanted to show respect on behalf of the entire country and represent the country in this moment of tragedy. She also stated that the President has been clear in speaking out against anti-Semitism and hate.